        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 11:41PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 1140 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 12 miles southwest of Ewing to near Ericson to
near Fort Hartsuff State Park. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Burwell, Bartlett, Ericson, Virginia Smith Dam, Cumminsville, Four
Corners, Pibel Lake State Recreation Area, Buffalo Flats, Deverre,
and Gables.

This includes Highway 281 between mile markers 132 and 157.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
north central Nebraska.</instruction>
